quote: While not all-together perfect, the film represents a monumental cinematic achievement that deserves to be placed high within the caliber of Nolan’s filmography.

quote: Interstellar is not Christopher Nolan's best film but what I will say is that you can't deny his ambition.

quote: As spectacular as it is flawed.

quote: One of the boldest science-fiction movies I've ever seen, both in narrative and visual terms. [Full review in Spanish]

publication.name: Cinemaficionados
title: Interstellar

quote: It was a blockbuster movie-going experience.
critic.name: Avaryl Halley
publication.name: Movie Bitches
title: Interstellar

quote: I guess the take away is all you need is love... and morse code?

publication.name: Movie Bitches
title: Interstellar

quote: Interstellar is, all in all, a very fine science fiction film.
critic.name: Kathi Maio
publication.name: The Magazine of Fantasy & Science Fiction
title: Interstellar

quote: Interstellar is 120 minutes of good movie stuffed into 170 minutes.
critic.name: Chris McCoy
publication.name: Memphis Flyer
title: Interstellar

quote: Interstellar is Nolan at his most humane. It's a good look for him.
critic.name: David Harris
publication.name: Spectrum Culture
title: Interstellar

critic.name: Katie Smith-Wong
publication.name: Flick Feast
title: Interstellar

critic.name: Kirsten Acuna
publication.name: Business Insider

quote: I found it emotionally moving and... what I wanted in a good sci-fi movie.

publication.name: rachelsreviews.net

title: Interstellar

quote: The summary work of Nolan: apotheosis of his signature where he attempts to merge the philosophical and emotional in entertaining genre packages.

publication.name: Patrick Nabarro

quote: It's the rare combination of a film that's both enjoyable in the theater and afterward, hashing through it over a drink
critic.name: Debbie Baldwin
publication.name: Ladue News
title: Interstellar

quote: Interstellar magnifies Nolan's style to a tremendous degree, but that also means enlarging his own flaws too.

publication.name: Alternative Lens

publication.name: DCist

publication.name: Bold Life (Hendersonville, NC)

publication.name: Screen Queens

critic.name: Rubén Rosario
publication.name: MiamiArtZine
title: Interstellar

title: Interstellar

quote: The result is a mess. But it's a beautiful mess, and one that I wouldn't want you to miss for the world.
critic.name: Annalee Newitz
publication.name: io9.com
title: Interstellar

quote: Watching Christopher Nolan fall short is still more exciting than watching most other directors succeed.
critic.name: Mark Keizer
publication.name: CineGods.com
title: Interstellar

quote: Nolan's refreshing love affair with self-determination goes too far.

publication.name: WORLD
title: Interstellar

quote: ...visually spectacular, complex, and both intellectually and emotionally stimulating...[Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Sebastian Zavala Kahn
publication.name: Cinencuentro
title: Interstellar

quote: Visually striking, with an impressive cast... [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Pablo O. Scholz
publication.name: Clarín
title: Interstellar

quote: Christopher Nolan's spectacular film is filled with frustration, anger, and guilt, and also strives for acceptance and even redemption.
critic.name: Uri Klein
publication.name: Haaretz
title: Interstellar

quote: Eye-popping visuals, an ambitious narrative, and a heart-racing soundtrack; one of Nolan's best
critic.name: Robert Kojder
publication.name: Flickering Myth
title: Interstellar

quote: Interstellar is why we go to the movies.
critic.name: Josh Terry
publication.name: Deseret News (Salt Lake City)
title: Interstellar

quote: This intergalactic extravaganza is clearly in a class by itself.
critic.name: Nancy Gail Reagan
publication.name: The Times of India
title: Interstellar

quote: Big Ideas served in a movie that is ultimately unsatisfying.
critic.name: Sarah Marrs
publication.name: Cinesnark
title: Interstellar

quote: With all the rampant think pieces questioning the probability of every science fiction film that comes out, it's comforting to across a movie that doesn't really claim to have any of the answers.
critic.name: Candice Frederick
publication.name: Reel Talk Online

publication.name: The Week
title: Interstellar

quote: Nolan does (to his credit) and his failure to engage us as fully as he intends... takes us to infinity and beyond, but it's likely you cared more about Buzz Lightyear than you will about anyone in Interstellar.
critic.name: Eleanor Ringel Cater
publication.name: Saporta Report (Atlanta)
title: Interstellar

quote: It's flawed, certainly, but its vision is undeniably appealing and ultimately the film's saving grace.
critic.name: Danielle Riendeau
publication.name: Polygon
title: Interstellar

quote: A film made with meticulousness and ambition, that achieves its tasks both narrative and visual with singular efficiency and grandiloquence that never feels forced. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Nicolás Ruiz
publication.name: Código espagueti
title: Interstellar

title: Interstellar

quote: Interstellar, though ambitious and thrilling at points, is too complicated and doesn't reach its full potential.
critic.name: Dwight Brown

title: Interstellar

critic.name: Camilla Long
publication.name: Sunday Times (UK)
title: Interstellar

quote: It is a wondrously beautiful movie, with intense sci-fi sequences, a solid and talented cast, and even some thought-provoking ideas. This is not one to be missed.
critic.name: David Fontana
publication.name: Film Inquiry
title: Interstellar

quote: Christopher Nolan is incredibly good at making science-fiction movies for people who think they don't like sci-fi.
critic.name: Gavia Baker-Whitelaw

title: Interstellar

quote: Interstellar never feels overly long despite its almost three hour running time. It also packs an emotional wallop, if you let it.
critic.name: Sonny Bunch
publication.name: Washington Free Beacon
title: Interstellar

quote: It's his 'White Album,' overlong and overwritten, corny and self-important, and also a great movie. And yes, it can be all of those things at once.

publication.name: Flavorwire
title: Interstellar

quote: Can we fly a spaceship through a galactic wormhole to Saturn? We haven't even put a man on Mars yet! It's another 342,077,666.43 miles from Mars to Saturn! Fuggeddaboudit!
critic.name: Mark Jackson
publication.name: Epoch Times
title: Interstellar

quote: Perhaps it would have been wiser to trim back on several of the ideas and present a more cohesive, not to mention coherent, story.
critic.name: George Byrne
publication.name: The Herald (Ireland)
title: Interstellar

quote: Interstellar feels like a collection of arresting moments and ideas that don't quite hang together.
critic.name: Paul Whitington
publication.name: Irish Independent
title: Interstellar

quote: The result is a flawed but highly engaging experience that is as frustrating as it is astonishing.
critic.name: Doug Whelan
publication.name: Irish Independent
title: Interstellar

quote: A blockbuster that's profound, poignant and exhilarating.
critic.name: Francesca Rudkin
publication.name: New Zealand Herald
title: Interstellar

quote: Too literal-minded, too conspicuous to leave us with a sense of doubt and apprehension.
critic.name: Kong Rithdee
publication.name: Bangkok Post
title: Interstellar

quote: Nolan's Interstellar waxes poetic about the universality of love and lingers beautifully on worlds beyond ours.
critic.name: Bill Newcott
publication.name: AARP Movies for Grownups
title: Interstellar

quote: A dynamic left-right combo of spectacle and heart that efficiently covers over the screenplay's various cracks and crevices.
critic.name: J. Olson
publication.name: Cinemixtape
title: Interstellar

quote: Interstellar needs to be seen on the biggest screen you can get your eyes on for maximum impact.
critic.name: Padraic McKiernan
publication.name: Sunday Independent (Ireland)
title: Interstellar

quote: When the essential property of film forces us to believe in an illusion, [Nolan] has become the least-spiritual director in contemporary cinema.
critic.name: Peter Labuza
publication.name: The Film Stage
title: Interstellar

critic.name: Emine Yildirim
publication.name: Today's Zaman (Turkey)
title: Interstellar

quote: I can't remember an apocalyptic film that's taken less interest in this planet as it's destroyed.
critic.name: Eileen Jones
publication.name: The Jacobin
title: Interstellar

quote: This is a film rife with mistakes that even a rookie director wouldn't make. How this ended up being made by Nolan blows my mind.
critic.name: John Rico
publication.name: About.com
title: Interstellar

quote: This is one of the most beautiful films I have ever seen.
critic.name: Richard Roeper
publication.name: Chicago Sun-Times
title: Interstellar

quote: [Interstellar] is a mighty science fiction epic built upon seriously shaky science. Yet that's hardly the point when this strives so hard, so achingly, to be profound. And very nearly is too.
critic.name: David 'Mad Dog' Bradley
publication.name: Rip It Up
title: Interstellar

quote: Interstellar may be a failure on a story level, but Nolan's visual virtuosity is still enough to take your breath away and root you to your chair.
critic.name: Kristian M. Lin
publication.name: Fort Worth Weekly
title: Interstellar

quote: Let's be plain. Christopher Nolan has made a lopsided soufflé of a film, but one with such fine ingredients you can hardly complain about the shape when you're enjoying the taste.
critic.name: Stuart McGurk
publication.name: GQ Magazine [UK]
title: Interstellar

quote: Interstellar dares it viewers to come along on a perilous adventure that is immersive, impressive, and intelligent.
critic.name: Nandini Ramnath
publication.name: Scroll.in
title: Interstellar

quote: Nolan is a well-appointed mainstream fabulist who uses a great deal of money and technology to no great artistic purpose.
critic.name: Rob Gonsalves
publication.name: eFilmCritic.com
title: Interstellar

quote: ...after building up the drama of personal sacrifice, it feels too much like a cheat no matter how many endings are tacked on before the credits...
critic.name: Kevin A. Ranson
publication.name: MovieCrypt.com
title: Interstellar

quote: It's just a really weird film, the strangest and most misguided fake-Spielberg picture since Super 8.
critic.name: Sean Burns
publication.name: Spliced Personality
title: Interstellar

quote: This is a film where complex concepts of quantum physics and powerful human emotions are inextricably intertwined and the ghost that haunts the farmhouse has both a scientific explanation and a sense of supernatural power.
critic.name: Sean Axmaker
publication.name: Parallax View
title: Interstellar

quote: Visual splendor does not entirely make up for failures in plotting and characterization.
critic.name: Wesley Lovell
publication.name: Cinema Sight
title: Interstellar

quote: Interstellar is a frustratingly flawed film that reaches for the stars but winds up lost in space.
critic.name: Isaac Feldberg
publication.name: We Got This Covered
title: Interstellar

quote: Interstellar is chockablock with philosophical ideas, visual effects and theoretical physics from Nolan and his brother, Jonathan, who co-wrote the script.
critic.name: Rob Lowman
publication.name: Los Angeles Daily News
title: Interstellar

quote: Interstellar is a grand gesture in every way. And yet, it's Nolan's most humane film to date.
critic.name: Dominick Suzanne-Mayer
publication.name: Consequence
title: Interstellar

quote: For all the themes intended to rocket our minds into a futuristic escape plan, it's too overloaded with hopelessness and bent logic to get off the ground.
critic.name: Jules Brenner
publication.name: Cinema Signals
title: Interstellar

quote: Nolan is one of the few directors with the ambition to tackle big topics -- like the fate of humanity or our need to explore -- and the artistic clout to bring that vision to a mass audience.
critic.name: Sean P. Means
publication.name: Salt Lake Tribune
title: Interstellar

quote: There are many words to describe Interstellar. Entertainment isn't one of them.
critic.name: Scott Marks
publication.name: San Diego Reader
title: Interstellar

quote: This sort of hammering, a determination that you'll "get it", distracts from Interstellar's effort to transport.
critic.name: Cynthia Fuchs
publication.name: PopMatters
title: Interstellar

quote: Though the family ties don't quite hold, Interstellar gives us an epic of space travel as desperate necessity, at a time when its science fiction hits perilously close to home.
critic.name: Genevieve Valentine
publication.name: Philadelphia Weekly
title: Interstellar

quote: You'll feel the cold on the Hoth-like ice planet. It's pure movie magic -- impressive and astonishing and deserving of all the out-of-this-world hyperbole. Too bad the rest of it is mostly empty space.
critic.name: Dana Barbuto
publication.name: The Patriot Ledger
title: Interstellar

quote: While it definitely feels as though Nolan over-reached and under-edited, there's enough eye candy and emotion to keep you from being bored.
critic.name: Scott Nash
publication.name: Three Movie Buffs
title: Interstellar

quote: This is a Nolan film, so nothing is simple -- or quick to the point. At nearly three hours, the film piles on the twists, wonky physics, heartfelt speeches and pseudoscience.
critic.name: AP Kryza
publication.name: Willamette Week
title: Interstellar

quote: Watching Nolan's latest attempt to create something artistic, intelligent and entertaining on such a massive scale, I couldn't help but think that with "Interstellar," he's outsmarted himself.
critic.name: Michael Smith
publication.name: Tulsa World
title: Interstellar

quote: "Interstellar" is flawed, but has the kind of scope that makes going to movies fun.
critic.name: Mal Vincent
publication.name: The Virginian-Pilot
title: Interstellar

quote: I urge you to stop seeking out information on this film, and instead wait until this Thursday and see it, on the biggest screen within reach. You won't be sorry.
critic.name: Paul Verhoeven
publication.name: The Vine
title: Interstellar

quote: McConaughey and his co-stars do a terrific job of underplaying the tech-nobabble and selling their individual moments... and Nolan's trademark big-picture confidence propels Interstellar through its near-three-hour running time with breathless style.
critic.name: Norman Wilner
publication.name: NOW Toronto
title: Interstellar

quote: You go in to Interstellar hoping to be mind-blown, thrilled, and smartened-up. Although it's beautifully made, brainy and sometimes insanely gorgeous, you may find yourself wondering what the big whoop was all about.
critic.name: Stephen Rebello
publication.name: Playboy Online
title: Interstellar

quote: As undeniably ambitious and technically accomplished as it is bloated, ponderous and ludicrous, Interstellar finds Christopher Nolan struggling in the shadow of Kubrick, Malick and other visionary filmic philosophers.
critic.name: Michael Leader
publication.name: Film4
title: Interstellar

quote: It's an enthralling, provocative, ambitious film.
critic.name: Brett McCracken
publication.name: Christianity Today
title: Interstellar

quote: Interstellar's themes are universal and some of the dialogue really resonates too.
critic.name: Graham Young
publication.name: Birmingham Mail
title: Interstellar

quote: I learnt a lot about wormholes and, while I can be entranced by the idea of saving the human race, I want a little bit of drama to go with it.
critic.name: Margaret Pomeranz
publication.name: At the Movies (Australia)
title: Interstellar

quote: This is not only a tremendously exciting space adventure... It's also a rich and thoughtful meditation on time and space and gravity.
critic.name: David Stratton
publication.name: At the Movies (Australia)
title: Interstellar

quote: "Interstellar" is a grand undertaking, but in shooting for the stars, it loses its footing. It goes to infinity and beyond, when infinity would have been plenty.
critic.name: Adam Graham
publication.name: Detroit News
title: Interstellar

quote: That the universe contains phenomena eons beyond us while at the same time intimately close is a beautiful concept and Interstellar seeks to orchestrate its own moment of revelation.
critic.name: Jordan Hiller
publication.name: Bangitout.com
title: Interstellar

quote: Interstellar is a visual feast that explores the universe and an intimate drama that explores why love and devotion are qualities that make the human race worth saving.
critic.name: Lori Hoffman
publication.name: Atlantic City Weekly
title: Interstellar

quote: There's a certain clumsiness to Nolan's longest and most personal film, a kind of earnest self-seriousness that opens it to parody and snark. But at its center beats a human heart.
critic.name: Philip Martin
publication.name: Arkansas Democrat-Gazette
title: Interstellar

quote: It's a fairly s----y science-fiction movie, but as a metaphor for love it's kind of great.
critic.name: Walter Chaw
publication.name: Film Freak Central
title: Interstellar

quote: Having set out to be a journey into what can hardly be depicted at all, Interstellar must find oblique ways of suggesting further imperceptible dimensions of the real. It is worth the journey to see what Nolan has constructed as a model of the unknowable.
critic.name: Geoffrey O'Brien
publication.name: Film Comment Magazine
title: Interstellar

quote: Big on ideas and concepts but falls apart in the 3rd act.
critic.name: Michelle Alexandria
publication.name: Eclipse Magazine
title: Interstellar

quote: A graceful, stirring epic and while it may not set new standards for the genre, it does give today's audiences a reminder of what visionary filmmaking looks like.
critic.name: Bruce Bennett
publication.name: Spectrum (St. George, Utah)
title: Interstellar

quote: A remarkable achievement in filmmaking that will have you on the edge of your seat
critic.name: Michael A. Smith
publication.name: MediaMikes
title: Interstellar

quote: Despite some awkward pacing, easy sentimentality, and pandering it's still hard to resist. It's not just Nolan's ambition that should be admired. He actually pulls off scene after scene of unforgettable drama in colossal scale, both in space and on Earth.
critic.name: Eric Melin
publication.name: Lawrence.com
title: Interstellar

quote: After the first hour, with its poignant depiction of humanity's decline, Interstellar always seems to be rebuilding its momentum, offering plenty to think about but little to hold on to.
critic.name: Ben Sachs
publication.name: Chicago Reader
title: Interstellar

quote: Ultimately, Interstellar shoots for the stars but barely gets us past the soundstage.
critic.name: Andy Crump
publication.name: Paste Magazine
title: Interstellar

quote: Christopher Nolan's latest exercise in devising narrative lines that run laboriously in different locations and on multiple timescales to no great effect, other than to tell you that love will find a way.
critic.name: Stuart Klawans
publication.name: The Nation
title: Interstellar

quote: The sentimentality and Hollywoodized convenience of the storytelling prevent this mostly admirable film from achieving the escape velocities of Kubrick or Tarkovsky.
critic.name: John Beifuss
publication.name: Commercial Appeal (Memphis, TN)
title: Interstellar

quote: [O]nce our explorers pass into another galaxy...things take on a new dimension of banality and the film, however magnificently conceived in visual terms, becomes just another space adventure.
critic.name: Jonathan Romney
publication.name: Film Comment Magazine
title: Interstellar

quote: A bombast-and-crisis megamovie, rocket-fuelled by gobbledygeek. The pummelling of plot turns and ratcheting of emotion-wrenches rarely relent. Forgets that we mere humans don't yet possess infinite patience for hyper-epic hokum.
critic.name: Brian Gibson
publication.name: Vue Weekly (Edmonton, Alberta)
title: Interstellar

quote: It's a film I didn't exactly enjoy and can't say I would recommend. And yet as an event, as a singular movie-watching opportunity, it's undoubtedly worthwhile.
critic.name: Christy Lemire
publication.name: ChristyLemire.com
title: Interstellar

quote: nothing if not grandly ambitious, and while that ambition is certainly admirable, especially in an industry choking on increasingly interchangeable big-budget franchises and starving for original ideas, it is also part of the film's downfall.
critic.name: James Kendrick
publication.name: Q Network Film Desk
title: Interstellar

quote: There's no denying that director Christopher Nolan's challenging space odyssey is exquisitely made. He's one of painfully few filmmakers whose every effort fills me with a sense of awe.
critic.name: Christopher Lawrence
publication.name: Las Vegas Review-Journal
title: Interstellar

quote: A combination of spectacular special effects, marginal physics and grindingly slow treacle, McConaughey pulls this one out of the fire.
critic.name: Ron Wilkinson
publication.name: Monsters and Critics
title: Interstellar

quote: The movie is complex and maddening, filled with concepts over the heads of most mere mortals, yet grounded in barely enough humanity to stimulate our senses.
critic.name: Bob Bloom

quote: If it's spectacle you want, then Interstellar delivers, particularly when viewed in Nolan's preferred 70mm Imax format.

quote: It's an experience.
critic.name: Sam Fragoso

quote: Interstellar is a marvel of congruency from the opening shot to the final frame.

title: Interstellar

quote: Nolan's Vision Exceeds his Grasp.
critic.name: Charles Koplinski
publication.name: Illinois Times

quote: Interstellar is not a terrible movie, it's just such a chore.

publication.name: East Bay Express

quote: This majestic film retains a human heart.

publication.name: Radio Times
title: Interstellar

quote: Fails to launch...

quote: Nolan creates overwhelming, often breathtaking suspense in a number of sequences.

title: Interstellar

quote: Uma obra inquestionavelmente problemática.
critic.name: Pablo Villaça
publication.name: Cinema em Cena

quote: Christopher Nolan's epic is visually stunning and offers some ingenious ideas on time and space as it plays on our darkest fears about the end of life on Earth.

quote: You thought Gravity was an immersive lost-in-space experience? Just you wait.

quote: Interstellar is terrible, wonderful, sensational, thrilling, imbecilic. In any order you want.

quote: If only the plot and the corny, exposition-heavy dialogue - where characters speak in fortune cookie - could hold up to the cinematography.

quote: In the age of shopping-centre cinema, Christopher Nolan builds cathedrals.

publication.name: Daily Telegraph (UK)

quote: With its intellectually stimulating ideas and profound emotional ballast, Interstellar makes a solid impact, albeit without the Wow Factor

title: Interstellar

quote: ... it's the best science fiction movie you're likely to see this year, and quite possibly one of the best films period.
critic.name: Daniel M. Kimmel

publication.name: MovieWeb

quote: Nolan's gigantic exercise soars and sinks

quote: Interstellar is not perfect, but it's the bold, electrifying and provocative cinema with rocket scientist smarts and a sentimental heart.

quote: "Interstellar" feels like someone else's film, a Spielberg retread.

title: Interstellar

quote: It's almost impossible to resist recommending Interstellar, but it's equally tough to deny a galactic sense of disappointment.

quote: A roller-coaster for the mind and spirit... Twenty years from now we may think of it as a classic, even if it takes a bit of time for it to sink in.

title: Interstellar

quote: [Nolan's] new picture is his biggest: biggest event, biggest spectacle, biggest pastiche, biggest disappointment.

quote: Twice as long as Gravity and half as good.

title: Interstellar

quote: A lot of sound and fury, signifying not much.

title: Interstellar

quote: From the grand master of films about the mysteries of human nature, a disappointing exploration of family, science, and human survival.

quote: Ambitious, provocative, thoughtful, and highly entertaining--all things considered (believe me, ALL things are considered), it holds together very well.

title: Interstellar

quote: an ambitious film, but it's difficult to get swept up in its sweep.
critic.name: Laura Clifford

quote: I was pumped up at the end.

publication.name: rachelsreviews.net

publication.name: Cinergética
title: The Martian

title: The Martian

quote: The Martian is a crowdpleaser, hopefully one that may inspire the next generation of space explorations.
critic.name: Nathalia Aryani
publication.name: San Diego Entertainer

critic.name: Abbie Bernstein
publication.name: Assignment X

critic.name: Jennifer Heaton
publication.name: Alternative Lens

critic.name: Johnny Gayzmonic
publication.name: Fanboys of the Universe
title: The Martian

publication.name: The Hollywood Outsider
title: The Martian

quote: A kind of Saving Private Ryan in space.
critic.name: Pat Padua
publication.name: DCist
title: The Martian

critic.name: Molly Templeton
publication.name: Eugene Weekly (OR)
title: The Martian

critic.name: Charles Mudede
publication.name: The Stranger (Seattle, WA)
title: The Martian

quote: "The Martian" is exactly what you expect it to be: tense, humorous and dramatic.
critic.name: Pamela Powell
publication.name: Daily Journal (Kankakee, IL)
title: The Martian

quote: Matt Damon could make a career out of playing marooned astronauts and I would be totally fine with that.
critic.name: Deirdre Crimmins
publication.name: Film Thrills
title: The Martian

quote: Maybe the film is so bright because the days are thirty-nine minutes longer on Mars than on Earth, the same thirty-nine minutes that should have been cut from this Friday-less Robinson Crusoe.
critic.name: A.S. Hamrah
publication.name: n+1
title: The Martian

quote: Scott only gets it half right, but the science lecture up to the go-for-broke finale, is scintillating in its own cerebral right.
critic.name: Tom Meek
publication.name: The ARTery
title: The Martian

critic.name: Mark Keizer
publication.name: CineGods.com
title: The Martian

critic.name: Camilla Long
publication.name: Sunday Times (UK)

critic.name: Robert Kojder
publication.name: Flickering Myth
title: The Martian

critic.name: Matthew Bond
publication.name: The Mail on Sunday (UK)
title: The Martian

quote: The Martian is not self-serious, and is a reminder that you can make a movie with real stakes, depth, and tension and still include humor-it does not have to be one or the other (I'm looking at you, Christopher Nolan).
critic.name: Sarah Marrs
publication.name: Lainey Gossip
title: The Martian

quote: ... this bloated by mostly entertaining chunk of shameless American triumphalism casts Matt Damon as Mark Watney...
critic.name: José Teodoro
publication.name: Cinema Scope
title: The Martian

critic.name: M. Faust
publication.name: The Public (Buffalo)
title: The Martian

quote: The Martian never loses sight of the fact that it is about a supreme test of will and intelligence and human triumph.
critic.name: tt stern-enzi
publication.name: Cincinnati CityBeat
title: The Martian

quote: To watch The Martian is to witness the development of one man's pedagogy of what it means to exist in the universe.
critic.name: Brooke Corso
publication.name: The Monitor (McAllen, TX)
title: The Martian

quote: The Martian would be a great engineering recruitment film - if it ever mentioned the word 'engineering.'
critic.name: Alex Heeney
publication.name: Seventh Row
title: The Martian

critic.name: Julia Alexander
publication.name: Polygon
title: The Martian

critic.name: Paul Whitington
publication.name: Irish Independent

critic.name: Tanya Sweeney
publication.name: The Herald (Ireland)

publication.name: HeyUGuys

publication.name: Brooklyn Magazine

critic.name: Dan Webster
publication.name: Spokesman-Review (Washington)

critic.name: John Powers
publication.name: Vogue
title: The Martian

critic.name: Aramide Tinubu
publication.name: Shadow and Act
title: The Martian

critic.name: Dwight Brown
publication.name: National Newspaper Publishers Association
title: The Martian

quote: It is at once a thoughtful, witty, intelligent, tense, and emotional experience, as beautiful in presentation as it is delightful in spirit.
critic.name: David Fontana

quote: It's true geek entertainment, not just in the sense that it's science fiction, but because it's about a group of smart, competent characters solving problems that pan out like lethal brain teasers.
critic.name: Gavia Baker-Whitelaw
publication.name: The Daily Dot
title: The Martian

quote: Director Ridley Scott and screenwriter Drew Goddard have managed to turn a series of math equations into exciting filmed entertainment.
critic.name: Sonny Bunch
publication.name: Washington Free Beacon
title: The Martian

critic.name: Sean Axmaker
publication.name: Seanax.com

critic.name: Jeff Beck
publication.name: The Blu Spot

critic.name: Max Weiss
publication.name: Baltimore Magazine
title: The Martian

quote: You may discover hearing songs that normally provoke in you a knee-jerk flailing at whatever source is playing them ('Turn it off!!!') will here make you feel strangely happy.
critic.name: Mark Jackson
publication.name: Epoch Times
title: The Martian

critic.name: Kaori Shoji
publication.name: Japan Times
title: The Martian

quote: The film is racked with clichés, but largely because of Damon's presence as a compact ball of energy and optimism, The Martian ends up a passably impressive tale of survival, fired with a curious mix of thrill and humour.

publication.name: Bangkok Post
title: The Martian

quote: It's just a cracklingly good entertainment, a crowd-pleaser that's compelling and emotional and even a little inspirational.
critic.name: Jason Bailey
publication.name: Flavorwire
title: The Martian

quote: The interplanetary tech geek gardening thriller of the year.
critic.name: Russell Baillie
publication.name: New Zealand Herald
title: The Martian

quote: I'm so glad the filmmakers let Watney let his nerd flag fly, and I hope this movie will inspire other filmmakers to do the same.

publication.name: RedEye
title: The Martian

quote: The most colossally mediocre sci-fi movie of the decade, all in pursuit of empty backslapping and a grade school level celebration of science.
critic.name: J. Olson
publication.name: Cinemixtape
title: The Martian

quote: The Martian marks a huge, and much-needed, achievement for Scott and for Damon, whose part further cements his status as one of the biggest actors today.
critic.name: Marija Djurovic
publication.name: Cairo360
title: The Martian

quote: Here's a space travel epic that digs deep into technicalities and still manages to be tremendously thrilling and fun.
critic.name: Edmund Lee
publication.name: South China Morning Post
title: The Martian

quote: Like Tom Hanks before him and Leonardo DiCaprio, Damon doesn't shrink from the burden of being alone onscreen for so much of the film-he owns it....
critic.name: James Plath
publication.name: Family Home Theater

quote: It's an adventure, pure and simple, in the tradition of Robinson Crusoe and Gulliver. And every bit as timeless.
critic.name: Bill Newcott

quote: When it comes time for the inevitable 'triumph-of-the-human-spirit' that necessitates this regurgitated survival narrative, all that computes is smugness and nationalism.
critic.name: Jaymes Durante

quote: Sci-fi is withouth a doubt the genre in which Ridley Scott feels at his most comfortable, and he finally delivers an entertaining movie worthy of his caliber, even if it's not a masterpiece. [Full Review in Spanish]
critic.name: Iván Belmont
publication.name: Konexión
title: The Martian

quote: The biggest surprise in Ridley Scott's latest film, The Martian , is that Damon is very funny, in a movie that you wouldn't have expected to have any laughs. So if you've been put off

publication.name: Jerusalem Post
title: The Martian

quote: The Martian may be light, but it's a fun ride out of this world.
critic.name: Matt Goldberg
publication.name: Collider
title: The Martian

quote: A rollicking space procedural that depends on some logic, and a great deal of luck.
critic.name: Jordan Raup
publication.name: The Film Stage
title: The Martian

quote: Probably The Martian proves to be an entertaining popcorn movie that pleases general audiences but is beyond of being as good as Alien and Blade Runner. [Full Review in Spanish]
critic.name: Oscar Uriel
publication.name: Cinema Movil
title: The Martian

quote: The ending is so farfetched that the suspension of disbelief dies long before anyone in the film ever does.
critic.name: Paul Chambers
publication.name: Movie Chambers
title: The Martian

quote: Will eventually find itself planted amongst the best in Ridley Scott's bulging anthology as it is perfectly paced, visually stunning, and mentally challenging
critic.name: Frank Wilkins
publication.name: Reel Reviews
title: The Martian

quote: Charming and exciting without ever losing sight of its tale of humanity, and science.
critic.name: Felix Vasquez Jr.
publication.name: Cinema Crazed
title: The Martian

quote: The Martian pushes the right emotional buttons and is a crowd-pleaser.
critic.name: Kevin Carr
publication.name: Fat Guys at the Movies
title: The Martian

quote: ...an often potent sci-fi drama that benefits substantially from Damon's almost impossible charismatic performance...

publication.name: New Yorker
title: The Martian

quote: Fascinating, feel-good and quite simply a hugely fun reason to head to the cinema.
critic.name: Alex Zane
publication.name: The Sun (UK)
title: The Martian

quote: Sci-fi maestro Ridley Scott is in his element employing the 3D format to dazzlling effect.
critic.name: Georgia Morgan
publication.name: Liverpool Echo
title: The Martian

quote: It's pretty sunny and often funny, a space oddity for a director not known for pictures with a sense of humor.
critic.name: Soren Andersen
publication.name: Seattle Times

publication.name: St. Paul Pioneer Press

quote: One of Ridley Scott's better films in years features one of Matt Damon's best performances.
critic.name: David Blaustein
publication.name: ABC News Radio

quote: The Martian is one of the films of the year so far.
critic.name: Mark Adams
publication.name: Daily Mirror (UK)

publication.name: AllMovie

publication.name: Ex-Press.com

publication.name: Time Out

quote: As the movie celebrates the astronaut's industry and intelligence (and the smarts of his NASA colleagues), it offers a riposte to the shortsightedness and science-denying attitudes of those unwilling to invest in solutions to the Earth's own dilemmas.

publication.name: Commercial Appeal (Memphis, TN)

quote: It isn't perfect, but The Martian is a triumph. From sound design to the visuals to watching the problem-solving unfold, it is astounding.
critic.name: Josh Lasser
publication.name: IGN Movies
title: The Martian

quote: cott's directorial skills are such that for much of the film you're rooted to your seat as Damon's Mark Watney struggles to survive.
critic.name: David Stratton
publication.name: The Australian
title: The Martian

quote: Riddley Scott proves again why he is the master of science fiction. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Jordi Batlle Caminal
publication.name: La Vanguardia (Spain)
title: The Martian

quote: dispenses with so much of the standard violent-action fare we have come to expect from science fiction films and instead returns the genre to its roots in the thrill of exploration and the wonders of science
critic.name: James Kendrick
publication.name: Q Network Film Desk
title: The Martian

quote: While this movie isn't as good as 'Interstellar', the science is more believable and the story is certainly a lot more straightforward and understandable, especially for the non-geeks amongst us.

publication.name: Laramie Movie Scope
title: The Martian

quote: It's not transcendent, but it is full of excitement. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Javier Ocaña
publication.name: El Pais (Spain)
title: The Martian

quote: A space adventure that surprises because of its fun and dynamic tone. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: José Arce
publication.name: LaButaca.net
title: The Martian

quote: Great visuals are not enough to fill the screen for the long running time of this predictable movie. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Daniel Krauze
publication.name: El Financiero
title: The Martian

quote: High octane entertainment. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Nicolás Ruiz
publication.name: Código espagueti
title: The Martian

quote: A magnificent movie and one of the most enjoyable films Scott has ever directed. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Mikel Zorrilla
publication.name: Espinof
title: The Martian

quote: Damon has a "care for me" gene that (one can argue) makes him one of the MVPs in Hollywood and he just takes us along with him on a ride that I, for one, wouldn't have missed.
critic.name: Jules Brenner
publication.name: Cinema Signals
title: The Martian

quote: It's a predictable and pleasing film. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Fernanda Solórzano
publication.name: Letras Libres
title: The Martian

quote: M﻿ore genial than suspenseful, more diverting than absorbing, but (thanks especially to Damon) consistently worthy of your good will.
critic.name: Stuart Klawans
publication.name: The Nation
title: The Martian

quote: Excellent film with spectacular visual effects and charming Matt Damon. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Mario P. Székely
publication.name: Siete24.mx
title: The Martian

quote: An excellent complement to the novel, simplifying the science without dumbing it down yet retaining the suspense and urgency of its interplanetary stranding.
critic.name: MaryAnn Johanson

title: The Martian

quote: Ridley Scott's The Martian may not be a great film, but it is great pop entertainment. For a full two hours and 20 minutes, it has the ability to hold an audience spellbound.
critic.name: Ken Hanke
publication.name: Mountain Xpress (Asheville, NC)
title: The Martian

quote: Ridley Scott shows a lighter touch this time in outer space as Matt Damon proves there is life on Mars and in this gem of a sci-fi adventure.

publication.name: Deadline Hollywood Daily
title: The Martian

quote: The Martian is no masterpiece, but it is a fine film from a talented director.
critic.name: Jeffrey M. Anderson
publication.name: Combustible Celluloid
title: The Martian

quote: Just as people began to write off veteran director Ridley Scott after a series of merely OK movies, the 77-year-old casually releases his most entertaining film in years.
critic.name: Rich Cline
publication.name: Contactmusic.com
title: The Martian

quote: Hollywood wastes billions of dollars each year trying to figure out how to entertain moviegoers. In reality, it's a pretty simple formula: Space travel + '70s-era radio hits = awesomeness.
critic.name: Christopher Lawrence
publication.name: Las Vegas Review-Journal
title: The Martian

quote: Deals with universal themes like survival, compassion, the importance of intelligence, scientific/technological know-how, cooperation, persistence and hope. It's truly a movie that matters.
critic.name: Betty Jo Tucker
publication.name: ReelTalk Movie Reviews
title: The Martian

quote: This is still a very nerdy movie, with lots of botany and physics and "we ran the numbers and it checks out," but most of the book's wonkiness is ironed out in favor of moving the story along more pleasingly for the science-allergic.
critic.name: Alissa Wilkinson
publication.name: Christianity Today
title: The Martian

quote: The humor and Damon's normal-guy qualities -- despite being a genius scientist -- make living on Mars all the more relatable to us. He and others also make math look cool. Geeks rule in this movie.
critic.name: Michael Smith
publication.name: Tulsa World

quote: While it boasts plenty of amazing effects and wide open vistas to justify its apportionment of IMAX screens, the film -- featuring a droll Matt Damon in the title role -- is a celebration of science, selflessness and good old-fashioned smarts.
critic.name: Zaki Hasan
publication.name: Philadelphia Weekly
title: The Martian

quote: If there's one fault to find in this inspiring tale, it's that Damon's just too smart and self-effacing to be real. But to say that would be too cynical: a trait this film is hiding away in the same cupboard, thankfully, with all of the schmaltz.
critic.name: Eric Melin
publication.name: Lawrence.com
title: The Martian

quote: Think Robinson Crusoe on Mars, though sans any primitive manservant named Friday.
critic.name: Kam Williams
publication.name: Baret News
title: The Martian

quote: The Martian isn't Scott's best film, but it's up there with the good ones. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Fausto Ponce
publication.name: Proceso
title: The Martian

quote: It rescues the carreer of a director and an actor who hadn't made anything interesting in the last couple of years. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Adrián Ruiz
publication.name: Excelsior
title: The Martian

quote: The Martian doesn't contain anywhere near the intellectual depth of Interstellar because it doesn't need to... it wants to stimulate a different muscle: The heart.
critic.name: Jon Espino
publication.name: The Young Folks
title: The Martian

quote: Matt Damon may play the marooned astronaut who fights to make it home in this feel-good sci-fi epic, but the big news is that director Ridley Scott is back.

quote: One the smartest, sweetest, and most satisfyingly suspenseful sci-fi films in years.
critic.name: Scott Weinberg

quote: You'd think they could break at least one cliché, but no. This narrative is gooey smooth like an oyster without a grain of sand with which to make a pearl.

publication.name: ColeSmithey.com

quote: ... light on wondering about our place in the universe and heavy on working out a way to get duct tape to seal an air leak.

publication.name: LarsenOnFilm

quote: The Martian is its own unique and wonderful beast, with a bizarre (in the best possible way) tone that is full of fun and wonder. It's a feel-good romp with lashings of science, a sci-fi flick with laughs, an ensemble comedy, a crowd-pleasing blockbuster.

quote: One of Scott's best films in recent history, if not THE best. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Sebastian Zavala Kahn

quote: The Martian works for casual audiences because its about aplicated science and not scientific theory, making it easier to work with. [Full rewiew in Spanish]

critic.name: Lucero Solórzano
publication.name: Excelsior
title: The Martian

quote: An impecably produced but ultimately uninspired movie. [Full rewiew in Spanish]
critic.name: Ernesto Diezmartinez
publication.name: Cine Vértigo

publication.name: LarsenOnFilm
title: Arrival

quote: Villeneuve, cinematographer Bradford Young, composer Jóhann Jóhannsson and editor Joe Walker dole out information and color it in knowing ways, building to third act revelations that make for profoundly moving film-making.
critic.name: Joe Gross
publication.name: Austin American-Statesman
title: Arrival

quote: I won't describe the aliens in detail here because the reveal is 87.4 per cent of the fun. I will say only that they're monstrous but also strangely balletic and tender.
critic.name: Deborah Ross
publication.name: The Spectator
title: Arrival

quote: Johan Johannsson's sonorous score is lovely; the performers spot on; and the philosophical concerns deep enough to confuse Christopher Nolan.
critic.name: Matt Glasby
publication.name: Flicks.co.nz
title: Arrival

quote: Where Close Encounters of the Third Kind gazed outward in awe at the universe, Arrival asks only how its mysteries might provide succour and illumination for us.
critic.name: Ryan Gilbey
publication.name: New Statesman
title: Arrival

quote: Through Adams and Renner's performances, we share dread, wonder, frustration, panic and transcendence as they begin to interact with the "Heptapod" aliens that evoke memories of the work of H.G. Wells and John Wyndham.
critic.name: Stephen Rebello
publication.name: Playboy Online
title: Arrival

quote: That "Arrival" works so well is in large part due to Adams, whose fear/eagerness in confronting beings from another world registers squarely with viewers. She can project deep emotions with a minimum of expression. It's all in the eyes.
critic.name: Robert W. Butler
publication.name: Kansas City Star
title: Arrival

quote: Exquisitely structured in surprising ways which only gradually reveal themselves, "Arrival" proves thoroughly mesmerizing. Conventional action is kept to a minimum, yet 2016 has scarcely seen such an exciting film. A hauntingly brilliant tour de force.
critic.name: Dustin Putman
publication.name: TheFilmFile.com
title: Arrival

quote: It is simultaneously old and new, revisiting many of these alien-invasion conventions but with unexpected intelligence, visual style and heart.
critic.name: Kenneth Turan
publication.name: Los Angeles Times
title: Arrival

quote: [A] cerebral wonder of a film.
critic.name: Valerie Kalfrin
publication.name: Film Racket
title: Arrival

quote: What's remarkable about Arrival is its contemplative core -- and, of course, Ms. Adams's star performance, which is no less impassioned for being self-effacing.
critic.name: Joe Morgenstern
publication.name: Wall Street Journal
title: Arrival

quote: Arrival is the latest in a long line of "first contact" sci-fi stories, and yet regardless of its familiar premise, its achievements are unique.
critic.name: Nick Schager
publication.name: The Daily Beast
title: Arrival

quote: Much of the film sees the camera focusing on Adams' face as her character studies and examines the aliens and their language. The beautiful subtleties of her performance depict what she's seeing and thinking, often without her using any words at all.
critic.name: Matt Miller
publication.name: Esquire Magazine
title: Arrival

quote: How far from reality is this hypothetical scenario? It doesn't seem too far removed...
critic.name: Mark Dujsik
publication.name: Mark Reviews Movies
title: Arrival

quote: Yes, there is something resembling a traditional climax, but it doesn't come at the expense of the ethereal tone established by Villeneuve. In this time of political upheaval, it's a welcome tonic.
critic.name: T'Cha Dunlevy
publication.name: Montreal Gazette
title: Arrival

quote: A familiar story about a close encounter, though well crafted and unusually moody.
critic.name: Rafer Guzman
publication.name: Newsday
title: Arrival

quote: Don't worry if you can't follow every detail... Just go along for the ride with Adams, a genuinely great screen actress who anchors this movie with a beautiful, deep-souled performance that should be up for all the major prizes.
critic.name: John Powers
publication.name: Vogue
title: Arrival

quote: After a mildly bumpy middle, the ending lands emotionally and safely in a surprisingly beautiful and satisfying climax.
critic.name: Jeff Simon
publication.name: Buffalo News
title: Arrival

quote: In its low-key lyricism with glimpses into the epiphanic, this is a beautifully controlled movie.
critic.name: Nigel Andrews
publication.name: Financial Times
title: Arrival

quote: More brain-teaser than action film, this is an elegantly-wrought piece of thinking-person's science fiction...that plays with convention in unexpected and enthralling ways.
critic.name: Frank Swietek
publication.name: One Guy's Opinion
title: Arrival

quote: ARRIVAL is likely to become a modern day sci-fi classic.
critic.name: JimmyO
publication.name: JoBlo's Movie Network
title: Arrival

quote: By the time it ends, Arrival is a story that could only be told in the science-fiction genre, and the result is a beautiful narrative that you find has been telling you things about itself without you ever realizing it.
critic.name: Britton Peele
publication.name: Dallas Morning News
title: Arrival

quote: Fine, full-bodied filmmaking, with a sense of the alien-ness out there in the universe that flatters our intelligence while making us feel tantalizingly small.
critic.name: Ty Burr
publication.name: Boston Globe
title: Arrival

quote: Arrival is not a linear adventure of the mind, and it is a film probably best seen twice.
critic.name: Richard Roeper
publication.name: Chicago Sun-Times
title: Arrival

quote: Muted, measured and meditative, "Arrival" brings taste and restraint to a genre in the midst of a mini golden age: It comes in peace.
critic.name: Ann Hornaday
publication.name: Washington Post
title: Arrival

quote: Working from a screenplay by Eric Heisserer, director Denis Villeneuve creates a richly imagined world in which the theme of extraterrestrial outreach is addressed with a refreshing dignity.
critic.name: Calvin Wilson
publication.name: St. Louis Post-Dispatch
title: Arrival

quote: [A] terrific, haunting film that plays with our expectations - and rewards us with satisfying left turns.
critic.name: Bill Goodykoontz
publication.name: Arizona Republic
title: Arrival

quote: Villeneuve draws on Close Encounters of the Third Kind for his portrayal of scientists and soldiers groping for answers and, more generally, of the celestial playing out in highly personal terms.
critic.name: J. R. Jones
publication.name: Chicago Reader
title: Arrival

quote: Amy Adams is spot on in the lead role, admirably keeping the story on track and not seizing a flashy scene for the consideration of Oscar voters. She does everything right.
critic.name: Edward Johnson-Ott
publication.name: NUVO Newsweekly
title: Arrival

quote: One of a handful of movies that have legitimately fooled me; not with an abrupt twist but a dawning awareness of where it's going thematically, how deeply and how distanced from sci-fi as usual.
critic.name: Steve Persall
publication.name: Tampa Bay Times
title: Arrival

quote: What really stays stuck in your memory long after the movie has ended and the world has been saved, or just as likely not, is the ache at the heart of the world Villeneuve has created.
critic.name: Marc Savlov
publication.name: Austin Chronicle
title: Arrival

quote: An alien-invasion fantasy that operates within the genre at the same time as it subverts it - large-scale movie-star sci-fi filtered through the tricky, esoteric lens of art-house cinema.
critic.name: Leah Greenblatt
publication.name: Entertainment Weekly
title: Arrival

quote: "Arrival" is the sort of superficially profound movie that initially seems deep and weighty but stops making sense the moment you put down the bong.
critic.name: Rene Rodriguez
publication.name: Miami Herald
title: Arrival

quote: How many sci-fi movies actually give you ideas to argue about anymore? How many sci-fi movies give you ideas at all?
critic.name: Stephen Whitty
publication.name: Newark Star-Ledger
title: Arrival

quote: Ostensibly an alien story, "Arrival" tackles, with confidence and clarity, conflict in whether mankind will acquiesce or aggress, come together or cloister tighter, compromise or collapse. Here is a masterwork of both the moment and the millennium.
critic.name: Nick Rogers
publication.name: The Film Yap
title: Arrival

quote: A whip-smart sci-fi movie that powers through strongly and confidently on character, an emotional human story and a performance, instead of special effects.
critic.name: Neil Pond
publication.name: Parade Magazine
title: Arrival

quote: Arrival is arguably the most emotional, thought-provoking and visceral experience [Villeneuve has] crafted yet.
critic.name: Jack Giroux
publication.name: Bullz-Eye.com
title: Arrival

quote: Arrival is at its best when pregnant with the suspense of the possible, when the unidentified stationary objects bear no trace of their intentions. But the film becomes less intriguing as the story's direction moves from teasingly opaque to crystal-clear.
critic.name: Cary Darling
publication.name: Fort Worth Star-Telegram/DFW.com
title: Arrival

quote: Cerebral. Serene. Entrancing.
critic.name: Roger Moore
publication.name: Movie Nation
title: Arrival

quote: Arrival has come, like a visitor from the cosmos, to blow minds and break hearts.
critic.name: A.A. Dowd
publication.name: AV Club
title: Arrival

quote: So much of the pleasure of Denis Villeneuve's poignant science-fiction drama "Arrival" lies in watching Amy Adams figure things out.
critic.name: Moira MacDonald
publication.name: Seattle Times
title: Arrival

quote: Remember all that crap at the end of Interstellar where it tried to get clever but failed horribly? This pulls it off.
critic.name: Matt Neal
publication.name: ABC Radio (Australia)
title: Arrival

quote: A terrific example of how to put the 'science' back into 'sci-fi' without compromising pace or action.
critic.name: Tom Glasson
publication.name: Concrete Playground
title: Arrival

quote: Feels deeply, cloyingly influenced by others. It's the last act of Close Encounters of the Third Kind meets Contact meets Inception / Interstellar meets The Tree of Life ... tries too hard to make you cry to actually make you cry.
critic.name: CJ Johnson
publication.name: Film Mafia
title: Arrival

quote: If Arrival succeeds at the box office, it will shine as a beacon in favor of not dumbing down every production to appease the distracted and disinterested masses.
critic.name: James Berardinelli
publication.name: ReelViews
title: Arrival

quote: Arrival is at once majestic and melancholy. It's a grand endeavor, and Adams, at the center of it all, brings pluck and smarts and a deep-seated sorrow to her role. This is her movie, no doubt.
critic.name: Steven Rea
publication.name: Philadelphia Inquirer
title: Arrival

quote: Arrival never fully escapes from the bounds of its source material.
critic.name: Sarah Cullen
publication.name: Film Ireland Magazine
title: Arrival

quote: It can seem at times intellectually impenetrable and breathily pretentious. But a movie that makes you think? What a novel idea.
critic.name: Michael Heaton
publication.name: Cleveland Plain Dealer
title: Arrival

quote: [Adams] delivers a heart-wrenchingly beautiful performance using her ability to communicate a half-dozen emotions just standing still... But director Denis Villeneuve sometimes gets lost in repetition and blind alleys.
critic.name: Mark Kennedy
publication.name: Associated Press
title: Arrival

quote: Adams' performance as Dr Louise Banks is terrific. She's the affecting emotional core of this. Especially once she starts her own close encounters with the inhabitants of the ship hovering above rural Montana.
critic.name: Russell Baillie
publication.name: New Zealand Herald
title: Arrival

quote: Elegant and ambitious, this sci-fi mystery is designed to take on life's biggest questions in the most intimate way.
critic.name: Joanna Langfield
publication.name: The Movie Minute
title: Arrival

quote: This deeply thoughtful, profoundly compassionate sci-fi movie beautifully mixes realism with a sense of wonder. It keeps its mysteries at bay, and, amazingly, doesn't disappoint when all is revealed.
critic.name: Jeffrey M. Anderson
publication.name: Common Sense Media
title: Arrival

quote: This rather wonderful science-fiction drama is very much a next-century companion piece to Steven Spielberg's 1977 classic Close Encounters Of the Third Kind.
critic.name: Leigh Paatsch
publication.name: Herald Sun (Australia)
title: Arrival

quote: Arrival is reaching for something it can't quite grab hold of. But it comes a whole lot closer than most.
critic.name: Vicky Roach
publication.name: Daily Telegraph (Australia)
title: Arrival

quote: Arrival is a weird flick, slow and tedious, too metaphysical for Rod Serling's The Twilight Zone and most likely to appeal to people who like to play video games and solve puzzles.
critic.name: Rex Reed
publication.name: Observer
title: Arrival

quote: ...[A] message drama disguised as a science-fiction adventure. Somber and slow-paced, it has been engineered more for the mainstream than fanboys.
critic.name: Daniel Eagan
publication.name: Film Journal International
title: Arrival

quote: Adams is convincing and smart-seeming, bringing appropriate queasiness to the position of being a college professor drawn into a rough military world.
critic.name: Allen Salkin
publication.name: New York Daily News
title: Arrival

quote: ...a more thoughtful, more intelligent science fiction film than the mainstream usually offers.
critic.name: Matthew Lowe
publication.name: FILMINK (Australia)
title: Arrival

quote: No writer or wordsmith or anyone who has studied language will be able to resist this film. In the eyes of Arrival, language can do more than connect disparate peoples, but change our very perspective on everything.
critic.name: Witney Seibold
publication.name: CraveOnline
title: Arrival

quote: Arrival is unlike any science fiction film you have seen. It builds like a slow boil into a deeply cerebral, emotionally expansive journey.
critic.name: Julian Roman
publication.name: MovieWeb
title: Arrival

quote: Arrival arrives at a good time, as something of a salve for the ugly discourse going on and a reminder to us that thinking big is really worthwhile.
critic.name: Tony Hicks
publication.name: San Jose Mercury News
title: Arrival

quote: I have seen no movie to which I felt more deeply connected this year. But I won't tell you exactly why. To discuss most particulars of this movie is to defeat its purpose.
critic.name: Lawrence Toppman
publication.name: Charlotte Observer
title: Arrival

quote: A science-fiction masterpiece that's largely about our perceptions of time and our struggles to communicate...unexpectedly romantic and profound in its deeper concerns, by exploring the happy-sad nature of existence itself, of being born to die.
critic.name: Peter Canavese
publication.name: Groucho Reviews
title: Arrival

quote: Intelligent, intense, grownup science fiction that will thrill genre lovers and satisfy fans of moving human drama. A beautiful, thought-provoking film.
critic.name: MaryAnn Johanson
publication.name: Flick Filosopher
title: Arrival

quote: Enlightening, inspiring, sci-fi allegory for our times - one of the year's best!
critic.name: Susan Granger
publication.name: SSG Syndicate
title: Arrival

quote: Don't be dismayed if you can't grasp every plot point quickly and easily. The images you see and things you hear need time to ruminate and be savored.
critic.name: Dwight Brown
publication.name: National Newspaper Publishers Association
title: Arrival

quote: The film develops an emotional undercurrent that becomes properly overwhelming in the final reel.
critic.name: Donald Clarke
publication.name: Irish Times
title: Arrival

quote: The sci-fi thriller not only subverts expectations in brilliant ways, it explores deeply felt themes of life, loss and love. In other words, it's light-years away from Independence Day 3.
critic.name: Mara Reinstein
publication.name: Us Weekly
title: Arrival

quote: The film's searching images counterpoint the hyper-articulate methodology of its characters' sense of imbalance and uncertainty.
critic.name: Sam C. Mac
publication.name: Slant Magazine
title: Arrival

quote: Arrival deserves our attention for being one of the best-paced, expertly shot and awe-inspiring sci-fi dramas to arrive in theaters in quite some time.
critic.name: Sean O'Connell
publication.name: CinemaBlend
title: Arrival

quote: Arrival is such a beautiful and thought-provoking film that it almost singlehandedly makes up for every bad aliens-coming-to-Earth film you've ever seen.
critic.name: Brian Truitt
publication.name: USA Today
title: Arrival

quote: Much of Arrival - the part that sticks closest to its source, egghead sci-fi cult figure Ted Chiang's "Story of Your Life" - is an eerie, tantalizing, altogether superb puzzler.
critic.name: David Edelstein
publication.name: New York Magazine/Vulture
title: Arrival

quote: Cerebral sci-fi with a Spielbergian sense of wonder.
critic.name: Harvey S. Karten
publication.name: Compuserve
title: Arrival

quote: Arrival has its heart in the right place. Who doesn't want smart sci-fi? Who wants to argue with a big budget drama about linguistics? And though the film is not more than sum of its parts, well, those parts are pretty great.
critic.name: Ben Croll
publication.name: indieWire
title: Arrival

quote: Arrival is an alien invasion movie for grown-ups; one that's lacking in action, explosions and all-out war, but heavy on tension, drama, and raw emotion.
critic.name: Chris Tilly
publication.name: IGN Movies
title: Arrival

quote: Atmospheric and thoughtful, it's an ideal choice to introduce hard sci-fi to a wider audience.
critic.name: Gavia Baker-Whitelaw
publication.name: The Daily Dot
title: Arrival

quote: If you like thoughtful, cerebral sci-fi films that are driven by ideas, you will be in for a treat.
critic.name: Stephen Carty
publication.name: Radio Times
title: Arrival

quote: A linguist, a physicist and a colonel walk into an alien spaceship. No joke. Just brilliance... Arrival is miraculous.
critic.name: Simon Miraudo
publication.name: Student Edge
title: Arrival

quote: Brainy yet expensive, "Arrival" flaunts its hope to be more like "Close Encounters of the Third Kind": slow, measured and filled with moments where the audience is supposed to collectively hush, open their jaws in unison and go awe.
critic.name: Matt Prigge
publication.name: Metro
title: Arrival

quote: It has big ideas and an unconventional structure, and it is rather engaging when it dives deep into the trade of language translation.
critic.name: Scott Mendelson
publication.name: Forbes
title: Arrival

quote: This isn't Close Encounters's wonder about the vastness of the universe; it's something trickier and more bittersweet about how we make our life decisions.
critic.name: Jesse Hassenger
publication.name: Brooklyn Magazine
title: Arrival

quote: Given that personal trauma is the prevailing throughline of Denis Villeneuve's filmmaking career so far, it's no surprise to find Arrival anchored by a familiar narrative motif.
critic.name: Adam Woodward
publication.name: Little White Lies
title: Arrival

quote: So sure is the stride of the narrative, and so bracing the air of expectation, that you feel yourself, like Louise, beginning to spin, and barely able to catch your breath.
critic.name: Anthony Lane
publication.name: New Yorker
title: Arrival

quote: For fans of dark, cerebral, Christopher Nolan type sci-fi or even time-related sci-fi this will be right up your alley.
critic.name: Lauren Warren
publication.name: Black Girl Nerds
title: Arrival

quote: In a breathtaking performance, Amy Adams grounds this hypnotizing sci-fi drama from Incendies director Denis Villeneuve, in which communication, purpose and time are key
critic.name: Louise Keller
publication.name: Urban Cinefile
title: Arrival

quote: For most of its running time, Arrival is entrancing, intimate, and moving - a sci-fi movie that looks not up at the stars but rather deep within.
critic.name: Bilge Ebiri
publication.name: Village Voice
title: Arrival

quote: Manages to transcend its genre elements and get to the heart of our existence. It exemplifies the power of love and sorrow to work as markers for our lives.
critic.name: Cameron Williams
publication.name: Graffiti With Punctuation
title: Arrival

quote: Arrival is Villeneuve's The Day The Earth Stood Still or Close Encounters Of The Third Kind, and somehow he makes it true to the tropes while also feeling like something new.
critic.name: Dan Jolin
publication.name: Empire Magazine
title: Arrival

quote: An intense film that make us consider not only what it means the arrival of the visitors, but how this will alter our reality. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Miguel Ravelo
publication.name: Correcámara
title: Arrival

quote: An outstanding sci-fi film with an intergalactic language lesson.
critic.name: Bill Stamets
publication.name: Chicago Sun-Times
title: Arrival

quote: With performances that have spanned a vast net of quirky and strong supporting players (i.e. "Junebug" and "The Fighter"), Amy Adams has emerged as a fully realized leading lady.
critic.name: Clayton Davis
publication.name: AwardsCircuit.com
title: Arrival

quote: The themes of the film are intricate, navigating ideas of love, loss and perception but Eric Heisserer - adapting from the short story The Story Of Your Life by Ted Chiang - keeps the exposition manageable.
critic.name: Amber Wilkinson
publication.name: Eye for Film
title: Arrival

quote: A super-smart sci-fi that'll blow your mind and have you on the edge of your seat without recourse to explosions or souped-up fighter jets.
critic.name: Matt Maytum
publication.name: Total Film
title: Arrival

quote: All this theoretical stuff is offset by some nicely unfussy performances... Still, the flick could use a little less conversation and a little more action.
critic.name: Adam Sweeting
publication.name: The Arts Desk
title: Arrival

quote: Denis Villeneuve's Arrival is that rare beast: an awe-inspiring sci-fi that delivers both spectacle and smarts.
critic.name: Jamie Dunn
publication.name: The Skinny
title: Arrival

quote: [Villeneuve] pushes the boundaries on what a sci-fi film really can be.
critic.name: Amy West
publication.name: International Business Times
title: Arrival

quote: Some grossly overstated dialogue keeps an immensely fascinating story and inventive visualization of a human-alien struggle to communicate from touching our tenderest sci-fi cinema soft-spots.
critic.name: Josef Braun
publication.name: Vue Weekly (Edmonton, Alberta)
title: Arrival

quote: A captivating story about an admirable protagonist in a fantastic position at the heart of a wonderful situation could actually make the world a better place.
critic.name: Fred Topel
publication.name: We Live Entertainment
title: Arrival

quote: It celebrates the very best traits of humanity ... while also encouraging us to confront life's biggest questions. This is filmmaking at its most powerful and profound.
critic.name: Nikki Baughan
publication.name: The List
title: Arrival

quote: Arrival can be mentioned in the same breath as 2001, Solaris and Contact. [Full review in Portuguese.]
critic.name: Pablo Villaça
publication.name: Cinema em Cena
title: Arrival

quote: Like all the best sci-fi, Arrival isn't really about aliens. It's about people. It's about ideas. But instead of hammering you over the head with those ideas in a bid to show how clever-clever it is, the film lets the story and characters do the talking.
critic.name: Mayer Nissim
publication.name: Digital Spy
title: Arrival

quote: Denis Villeneuve's latest is smart, hopeful, and intimately devastating science fiction.
critic.name: Rob Hunter
publication.name: Film School Rejects
title: Arrival

quote: Arrival is one of the best films of the year.
critic.name: Alan Cerny
publication.name: ComingSoon.net
title: Arrival

quote: The sheer emotional heft is downright staggering. Movies like this are what I'm here for.
critic.name: Jason Bailey
publication.name: Flavorwire
title: Arrival

quote: With Arrival, Denis Villeneuve communicates the wonder of a Steven Spielberg alien movie within a decidedly hard sci-fi milieu.
critic.name: Jake Cole
publication.name: Slant Magazine
title: Arrival

quote: A film of rare vision and beauty, Arrival is easily the most intelligent blockbuster released this year-and maybe any year.
critic.name: Noah Gittell
publication.name: Nerdist
title: Arrival

quote: Watching Adams attempt to teach the aliens English is remarkably gripping, aided by some genuinely breath-taking shots.
critic.name: Stephen Mayne
publication.name: PopMatters
title: Arrival

quote: The combination of science and emotions that Nolan wanted to deeply explore with Interstellar, it's fully reached in this film. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Arturo Aguilar
publication.name: Rolling Stone Mexico
title: Arrival

quote: Arrival proves to be much more than the standard first contact flick, and Villeneuve maintains his track record of turning all expectations of genre on their head.
critic.name: Sasha James
publication.name: The Mary Sue
title: Arrival

quote: The kind of movie that Christopher Nolan wanted to accomplish with Interstellar. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Oscar Uriel
publication.name: Cinema Movil
title: Arrival

quote: An existentialist and theorical film similar to Inception or Interestellar. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Carlota Mosegui
publication.name: Otroscines.com
title: Arrival

quote: Quite simply, Arrival is one of the most extraordinary, affecting films of the year, a delicate balance between intellect and passion, finding ways to entertain while opening one's mind up to possibilities.
critic.name: Jason Gorber
publication.name: That Shelf
title: Arrival

quote: The extraordinary success of Arrival is that it combines its bravura style and grand sci-fi questions with tremendous emotional intelligence and a heart so full it's ready to burst.
critic.name: Bryan Bishop
publication.name: The Verge
title: Arrival

quote: Sophisticated sci-fi - stunningly well-crafted and acted.
critic.name: Chris Bumbray
publication.name: JoBlo's Movie Network
title: Arrival

quote: Be patient. Arrival falls just short of perfect thanks to an expositional hiccup midway through the film and a climax that hinges on a borderline-hokey revelation, but the end will more than justify these ever so slightly sloppy means.
critic.name: Sarah Kurchak
publication.name: Consequence
title: Arrival

quote: Villeneuve has crafted a compelling tale which explores humanity's flaws, our own fears and impatience, in a way that is scarily realistic.
critic.name: Stefan Pape
publication.name: HeyUGuys
title: Arrival

quote: Arrival challenges viewers to a brainier sci-fi conundrum than they're used to, which makes for an intellectual breath of fresh air.
critic.name: Matt Donato
publication.name: We Got This Covered
title: Arrival

quote: Arrival is quite pretentious ... but it's the good kind. It's the smart kind.
critic.name: Mike Ryan
publication.name: Uproxx
title: Arrival

quote: A film that forces viewers to reconsider that which makes us truly human, and the impact of grief on that timeline of existence.
critic.name: Brian Tallerico
publication.name: RogerEbert.com
title: Arrival

quote: A cerebral and emotionally resonant examination of language through the genre of science fiction.
critic.name: Edward Douglas
publication.name: Den of Geek
title: Arrival

quote: This is hard science fiction made by an artist - which means big questions, impossible concepts and difficult choices.
critic.name: Norman Wilner
publication.name: NOW Toronto
title: Arrival

quote: It's heartening to encounter a science fiction thriller that is ready to deal with abstract ideas.
critic.name: Geoffrey Macnab
publication.name: Independent (UK)
title: Arrival

quote: Arrival has the heft of a literary airport novel, with enough poetry and pathos to elevate it above Michael Crichton.
critic.name: Richard Lawson
publication.name: Vanity Fair
title: Arrival
